# Conventional deny-list. The repo now lives at ~/.dotfiles (external) and holds
# only what we put here: the macos/ and linux/ tiers, shared lib/, setup.sh, and
# repo meta. No unmanaged ~/.config junk shares this root anymore, so the old
# allowlist gymnastics (ignore *, then ! every managed dir) are gone — everything
# is tracked by default and we deny-list only cruft, logs, and runtime state.

# ── OS / editor cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# ── Bootstrap runner logs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Runners tee each unit to <script>.log and delete it on success; a retained log
# means that unit failed. Transient either way — never tracked.
**/.setup.sh.log
**/*.sh.log

# ── Runtime / generated state routed into the repo via whole-dir symlinks ─────
# Because ~/.config/<app> is a symlink into a tier dir, anything an app WRITES
# into its config dir lands in this working tree. Keep per-machine state out of
# git (or fold it per-file to ~/.local/state — see design.md). Globbed with **/
# so the rules match under both macos/ and linux/.
**/zsh/.zshrc.zwc
**/zsh/*.zwc
**/zsh/.zcompdump*
**/zsh/.zsh_history
**/zsh/.zsh_sessions/
**/fish/fish_variables
**/micro/backups/
**/micro/buffers/
**/micro/log.txt
**/zed/prompts/

# ── Machine-local / secret-bearing ───────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# ── OpenSpec (local-only change tooling) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Change proposals/specs are working notes, not part of the deployed dotfiles.
openspec/

# ── Caches ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ── graphify-out: track only the queryable graph (union-merged via
# .gitattributes). The rest is machine-specific (.graphify_python/.graphify_root
# hold absolute paths) or regenerable locally by the git hook (graph.html,
# GRAPH_REPORT.md), so it stays ignored. NOTE: after this restructure the tracked
# graph.json paths are stale — re-run `graphify update .` post-migration.
graphify-out/*
!graphify-out/graph.json
